#. REF: nya28, sc28
msgctxt "mn68:28.1"
msgid "Iti kho, anuruddhā, tathāgato na janakuhanatthaṃ na janalapanatthaṃ na lābhasakkārasilokānisaṃsatthaṃ na ‘iti maṃ jano jānātū’ti sāvake abbhatīte kālaṅkate upapattīsu byākaroti: "
msgstr "So it’s not for the sake of deceiving people or flattering them, nor for the benefit of possessions, honor, or popularity, nor thinking, ‘So let people know about me!’ that the Realized One declares the rebirth of his disciples who have passed away: "

msgctxt "mn68:28.2"
msgid "‘asu amutra upapanno, asu amutra upapanno’ti. "
msgstr "‘This one is reborn here, while that one is reborn there.’ "

msgctxt "mn68:28.3"
msgid "Santi ca kho, anuruddhā, kulaputtā saddhā uḷāravedā uḷārapāmojjā. "
msgstr "Rather, there are gentlemen of faith who are full of joy and gladness. "

msgctxt "mn68:28.4"
msgid "Te taṃ sutvā tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharanti. "
msgstr "When they hear that, they apply their minds to that end. "

msgctxt "mn68:28.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ taṃ, anuruddhā, hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "That is for their lasting welfare and happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "mn68:28.6"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn68:28.7"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā anuruddho bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Anuruddha and friends were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn68:28.8"
msgid "Naḷakapānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. "
